The evidence with the title 'The 30 percent rule: why is this the benchmark for affordable ... ' says Aug 4, 2015  ... Anyone who has looked for an apartment to rent or a home to buy has probably heard the rule of thumb that you should n't spend more than 30 % of your income  ... We should expect housing to take up an increasingly large part of our incomes : as the economy grows , the cost of many goods are going to fall. 
